| Indigenous Rights           | Uphold rights and knowledge of Indigenous peoples                               | Governments, Indigenous groups     |
| Financing Conservation      | Increase public and private funding with safeguards                             | Governments, private sector        |

## Conclusion

Protecting nature requires a multifaceted approach involving policy advocacy, scientific research, sustainable practices, community engagement, and adequate financing. Individual actions, when combined with systemic changes, can significantly contribute to conserving biodiversity and ecosystem services. Emphasizing nature-based solutions and respecting Indigenous rights will enhance the sustainability and equity of conservation efforts. To meet ambitious global targets such as protecting 30% of Earth’s land and oceans by 2030, coordinated action across all levels of society and sectors is imperative.

